# Core Standards

- Read and respect the local planning docs:
  - `@docs/plan.md` (handoff / execution overview)
  - `@docs/spec.md` (behavior and contracts)
  - `@docs/conventions.md` (naming, migrations, error codes, release policy)
  - `@docs/NON_OBVIOUS.md` and `@docs/model-routing.md`
  - `@docs/decisions/ADR-*.md`
- Preserve the planning vocabulary and IDs exactly:
  - Requirements: `FR-*`, `NFR-*`
  - Invariants and safety: `INV-*`, `SAFE-*`
  - Errors and changes: `AE-*`, `CR-*` (change requests)
  - Tests: `TC-U-*`, `TC-I-*`, `TC-C-*`, `TC-E2E-*`, `TC-S-*`, `TC-P-*`, `TC-Q-*`
- Prefer minimal, vertical slices that match `@docs/execution-plan.md` and `@docs/scope-lock.md`.
- Never silently expand scope beyond the locked PH-A features; point back to scope lock first.

